Giantkillers Bradford - who claimed a shock 4-2 victory against Premier League leaders Chelsea at Stamford Bridge - will host Sunderland or Fulham.

West Brom and West Ham will play out an all Premier League affair at the Hawthorns while Midlands duo Aston Villa and Leicester will meet at Villa Park. 

Derby will host Championship rivals Reading while Stoke, who beat Rochdale 4-1 on Monday, will travel to Blackburn Rovers.

All ties will take place across the weekend of 14 and 15 February 2015.  

